## Dashboard Interaction Modes

### Observer Mode (Read-Only)

**Access**: Public, media, oversight, researchers

**Capabilities**:
- View aggregate integrity metrics
- Access anonymized reasoning traces
- Monitor system health trends
- Download transparency reports

**Purpose**: Public accountability & trust building

---

### Steward Mode (Active Partnership)

**Access**: Certified stewards

**Capabilities**:
- All Observer Mode features
- Real-time intervention controls
- Steward load monitoring
- Decision approval/override
- Direct Chronicle annotation
- Filter lattice adjustments

**Purpose**: Active human-AI partnership

---

### Forensic Mode (Investigation)

**Access**: Investigators & compliance teams

**Capabilities**:
- Full Chronicle replay
- Detailed arbitration analysis
- Filter activation history
- Emotional calibration trace
- Multi-model comparison
- Incident reconstruction

**Purpose**: Root cause analysis & learning

---

## Telemetry Streams

### Incoming Telemetry

**Sources**:
- Reasoning checkpoints
- Filter activation logs
- Emotional signal vectors
- Model arbitration summaries
- Adversarial resilience events
- System stability delta
- Steward fatigue index shifts

**Processing**:
- Real-time aggregation
- Historical recording
- Pattern detection
- Alert generation

**Storage**:
- Hot data: Last 24 hours (real-time access)
- Warm data: Last 30 days (near-real-time)
- Cold data: 30+ days (archival, queryable)

---

### Outgoing Telemetry

**Destinations**:
- Dashboard visualization
- Chronicle storage
- Concordat network (aggregated)
- Compliance reporting systems
- Research data repositories

---

## Predictive Integrity Modeling

Cathedral uses telemetry to forecast:

| Prediction | Method | Outcome |
|------------|--------|---------|
| **Risk probability** | Trend analysis + pattern matching | Preventative intervention |
| **Drift trends** | Coherence deviation tracking | Early stabilization |
| **Emotional destabilization** | Emotional signal forecasting | Proactive calibration |
| **Model divergence** | Variance prediction | Pre-emptive arbitration |
| **Overload pressure** | Steward load trajectory | Automated relief |

**Philosophy**: Not reactive safety â€” **preventative governance**.

